      About this item

      • Smarter smartwatch: CZ Smart YouQ a proprietary wellness app built using research by NASA Ames Center and AI Models with IBM Watson Studio. YouQ helps wearers maximize their daily potential by learning the wearer’s unique Chronotype and daily rhythms. YouQ computes HR, SP02, fitness activity, sleep, alert scores to offer the consumer 24-hour forecast of alertness. Aggregating data will enable CZ Smart YouQ to cater to wearers personally allowing them to understand their body's rhythms.
      • Self-care advisor: YouQ uses a gamified Alert Monitor, based on NASA’s PVT+. CZ Smart YouQ uses Alert Monitor scores and sleep data to identify the wearer’s Chronotype, a morning go-getter, steady achiever, high-energy hustler?. YouQ helps you stay on track with an Hourly Power Score, an indicator of your cognitive and physical energy at a particular moment. Power Fixes will mitigate fatigue and improve alertness so you can optimize the day. Napuccino or liquid energy in your future
      • Preloaded: Wear OS by Google *compatible with iPhone and Android. Applications available via Play Store include CZ Smart YouQ App, Google Fit, Strava, Spotify, YouTube Music, Amazon Alexa. Features 24+ hour battery life (varies based on usage) achieves a full charge in just 40-minutes. Connections Bluetooth, Wi-Fi, GPS, and NFC. Sensors Gyroscope, altimeter, barometer, accelerometer, heart rate sensor, SP02, ambient light sensor, track activity, heart rate, cardio fitness, steps, sleep
      • Personalization, notifications, and more: The uniquely designed CZ Smart dials give hundreds of options to fully customize your watch face and receive the information you find most important. Stay focused all day while getting notifications on your watch for incoming calls, texts, emails and calendar notifications. The built-in speaker enables you to conveniently answer a call from your smartwatch. With Amazon Alexa built-in, CZ Smart makes it easy to tackle your daily tasks and organization.
      • Citizen Connected works with phones running on the latest version of Android (excluding Go Edition and phones without Google Play Store) or iOS, 24+ hour battery life, Qualcomm 4100+ chipset

Like the Always On display, not just wearing a dead black screen. Specially at dark place or at night easy to check time at a quick glance in your wrist. Again, make sure you tune the settings good and the life of battery should last you like 18-20hours of normal use not on a work out mode. My purpose for this watch is mainly casual daily usage, office, church and lots of notifications.

This is a keeper, have it in the last 2 days, glad I did Pre-order and my much awaited time did pay me up with complete satisfaction. Could not be more happier and how I can no longer express further joy.

Will update if anything stand out or issues. Looking forward for it to last longer. I would highly recommend this to anybody that is looking for a watch with class.

          1.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
          poor battery, lots of software bugs, not water resistant
          Reviewed in the United States on May 10, 2023
          Color: Silver
          Review updated 5/15/23: Good looking watch if you pair the blue watch with a silver band. battery only lasts half a day or a little more, on minimum usage. lots of software issues with YouQ software , sleep data does not update, takes lots of time and tries,... See more
          Review updated 5/15/23:

          Good looking watch if you pair the blue watch with a silver band.
          battery only lasts half a day or a little more, on minimum usage. lots of software issues with YouQ software , sleep data does not update, takes lots of time and tries, power score does not show up on the watch sometimes, although it shows in the app. In sleep, it always shows 0h for deep,light, REM sleep. never shows any values in YouQ app. sometimes the time stamps are also wrong. lag is response on the watch, sometimes it works ok and sometimes very slow. due to poor battery, not water resistant , returned it. may be in future, i suggest to do proper software verification/validation, lots of nuisance software bugs , make it water resistant, and battery life is important. can't keep charging the watch twice or sometimes 3 times a day (if need sleep tracking at night).

          Also, no automatic way of turning off the screen when going to bed. I had to enable theater mode to turn off the screen. If any sleep schedule options, then the screen would turn off automatically when bed time.

          Disappointed by the Gen 2 watch. I ordered it in January back when Amazon started taking orders. Just received it. As soon as I realized it is not even water resistant, I lost interest. Not asking for scuba diving, but a watch should be at least splash proof, basic sweat, washing hands etc. Just minimal. In my opinion, this is a serious design flow. If I were to chose between enabling phone calling on the phone vs making it water resistant, I would have chosen Water resistance capability.

          Citizen Connected app is very basic and primitive, and lacking basic functionality that other smart watch manufacturers are providing. It is running on Google Wear OS, but Google Wear OS can't be connected to this watch. Disappointing to see how limited and basic Citizen's app is.
          Watch faces are limited and only a few to choose from.
          Screen could have been brighter and better.
          I bought the silver and the blue. Silver is not what Citizen watches normally feel to wear. The band feels like wearing a chain. Not a good feel. Blue is much better in terms of bezel and the band. But the blue band is too rigid. There are nice bands our there that are durable and feels better. And guess who makes those, Citizen Watch Company.
          I have been a big fan of Citizen watches for decades. Never has a citizen watch disappointed. My latest purchase was Citizen Navihawk. World Class and Top Class watch. I have about a dozen different citizen watches. All are amazing and some are more than 20 years old and still going flawless. A company like Citizen manufacturing a smart watch, that is not on par with the build quality that Citizen offers on their normal watches.
          Battery life I have to check, but in one hours, I am down to 74% battery life. This is another area that a smart watch should do better. My Amazfit GTR 4 watch gives me about 12 days of continuous usage including sleep tracking, workouts, Always On display.
          I am really excited about the Power Gauge , Power Score, Power Fix, that the YouQ app has. I have yet to experience it. Fingers crossed. But as a constructive feedback, the app is 'dark background' only. No option to change it to a lighter more visually friendly background. I shall revisit this review in next a few weeks and if YouQ does what it promises, I may give this watch another star.

          Overall, disappointing experience with the Gen 2 watch. Lacking basics that a smart watch should offer in terms of a user friendly app experience, build quality, and battery life.

          I remain a big fan of Citizen watches. I grew up with this brand and highly regard it. This review is more of a constructive feedback for Citizen. Please use common sense. Less then mediocre app to experience the full potential of a watch, is a serious lacking in my opinion. Also, the workouts are limited to 2 only. Indoor and Outdoor. On my Amazfit watch, I have 150+ workouts, and several are auto starting.
          Review updated 5/15/23:

          Good looking watch if you pair the blue watch with a silver band.
          battery only lasts half a day or a little more, on minimum usage. lots of software issues with YouQ software , sleep data does not update, takes lots of time and tries, power score does not show up on the watch sometimes, although it shows in the app. In sleep, it always shows 0h for deep,light, REM sleep. never shows any values in YouQ app. sometimes the time stamps are also wrong. lag is response on the watch, sometimes it works ok and sometimes very slow. due to poor battery, not water resistant , returned it. may be in future, i suggest to do proper software verification/validation, lots of nuisance software bugs , make it water resistant, and battery life is important. can't keep charging the watch twice or sometimes 3 times a day (if need sleep tracking at night).

          Also, no automatic way of turning off the screen when going to bed. I had to enable theater mode to turn off the screen. If any sleep schedule options, then the screen would turn off automatically when bed time.

          Disappointed by the Gen 2 watch. I ordered it in January back when Amazon started taking orders. Just received it. As soon as I realized it is not even water resistant, I lost interest. Not asking for scuba diving, but a watch should be at least splash proof, basic sweat, washing hands etc. Just minimal. In my opinion, this is a serious design flow. If I were to chose between enabling phone calling on the phone vs making it water resistant, I would have chosen Water resistance capability.

          Citizen Connected app is very basic and primitive, and lacking basic functionality that other smart watch manufacturers are providing. It is running on Google Wear OS, but Google Wear OS can't be connected to this watch. Disappointing to see how limited and basic Citizen's app is.
          Watch faces are limited and only a few to choose from.
          Screen could have been brighter and better.
          I bought the silver and the blue. Silver is not what Citizen watches normally feel to wear. The band feels like wearing a chain. Not a good feel. Blue is much better in terms of bezel and the band. But the blue band is too rigid. There are nice bands our there that are durable and feels better. And guess who makes those, Citizen Watch Company.
          I have been a big fan of Citizen watches for decades. Never has a citizen watch disappointed. My latest purchase was Citizen Navihawk. World Class and Top Class watch. I have about a dozen different citizen watches. All are amazing and some are more than 20 years old and still going flawless. A company like Citizen manufacturing a smart watch, that is not on par with the build quality that Citizen offers on their normal watches.
          Battery life I have to check, but in one hours, I am down to 74% battery life. This is another area that a smart watch should do better. My Amazfit GTR 4 watch gives me about 12 days of continuous usage including sleep tracking, workouts, Always On display.
          I am really excited about the Power Gauge , Power Score, Power Fix, that the YouQ app has. I have yet to experience it. Fingers crossed. But as a constructive feedback, the app is 'dark background' only. No option to change it to a lighter more visually friendly background. I shall revisit this review in next a few weeks and if YouQ does what it promises, I may give this watch another star.

          Overall, disappointing experience with the Gen 2 watch. Lacking basics that a smart watch should offer in terms of a user friendly app experience, build quality, and battery life.

          I remain a big fan of Citizen watches. I grew up with this brand and highly regard it. This review is more of a constructive feedback for Citizen. Please use common sense. Less then mediocre app to experience the full potential of a watch, is a serious lacking in my opinion. Also, the workouts are limited to 2 only. Indoor and Outdoor. On my Amazfit watch, I have 150+ workouts, and several are auto starting.

          Beautiful watch, horrible software.
          Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2023
          Color: Blue
          I've been a Citizen fan for years. I own six of them. I'm drawn to their design language. My Nighthawk is my favorite piece because of build quality and the details on the face are just amazing to me. When I saw they made a smart watch, I thought, "Sweet! This... See more
          I've been a Citizen fan for years. I own six of them. I'm drawn to their design language. My Nighthawk is my favorite piece because of build quality and the details on the face are just amazing to me. When I saw they made a smart watch, I thought, "Sweet! This is going to be an awesome watch." When I opened the box, I liked what I saw. I was stoked for the blue color, mainly because many options are focused on red and I'm not a fan of red. The physical watch itself was very well built and looked amazing. The crown and buttons looked solid and the body was clean and crisp. I was pleased.

          I was sorely disappointed when I started that bad boy up. The default face design was as inspired as an 80's commuter car. No big deal, I'm sure the Citizen artisans decided a generic default was the way to ease old school watch buyers into the digital future. Nope. Every single face available through the watch and the accompanying app are equally uninspired. I hoped I could use Facer, an app that allows you to upload 3rd party digital faces to your smart watch, to spruce up the watch, but that didn't work. So I had a beautiful watch with an ugly watch face. Well at least there is some sweet NASA technology inside that will hopefully make up for the banal watch face.

          No idea, the battery life is ridiculously horrible. I charged up the watch out of the box to 100% and with in SIX HOURS the watch was asking to be put on battery saver mode. Six freakin' hours. Nope. Took the watch off and put it back in the box to send back to Amazon.

          My guess is the powers that be at Citizen wanted or were convinced to get into the smart watch business as it is profitable and the way the watch landscape is moving, but the people at the top are old school and don't want to "sully" their IP of the classic watch faces and designs for the new fangled technology. I'd say the physical design team did their best and it showed, but the tech side seemed to be hamstringed by unimaginative administrators. Very disappointing.

          I love this watch's look. It's a stealth smartwatch that looks like a dress/diver/chronograph but is a full-featured smartwatch. Sadly, its looks are its best point.

          Battery Life: By the end of the first day, I was running on fumes, down to 6% before I gave up. The good news was that it charges up quickly, in less than an hour or so, but not making it through a whole day is a deal breaker.

          Apps: My favorite apps are pretty simple: Stopwatch and Timer. Both of these apps work fine, except that after 10 seconds, they hide themselves and show the time display. I searched for a fix for this but never found it.

          Bezel: It doesn't turn. It's not a rotating bezel like you'd find on a dive watch, but just a fashion statement. Unfortunately, the statement is, "I fell for it."

          I love Citizen. My favorite watch is a CItizen Garrison military-style chronograph, but I wanted something digital that was easier to read elapsed time on. Sadly, this isn't it. I've ordered a Timex Ironman to do the job, but it won't be as pretty.
